   <taskbody>
      <context class="- topic/section task/context ">
         <p class="- topic/p ">You can monitor the validation status of your agreement. For programs with pending validations, the Status is set to <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Pending Validation</uicontrol>. You cannot make any changes to the program when the validation process starts and the program is in pending validation state. You can monitor the validation status and also you can view the validation error in the Validation tab of the agreement program list view. For programs that fail validation, you can view and download the error file to know the reason behind the failed validation. To view the validation error file,</p>
      </context>
      <steps class="- topic/ol task/steps ">
         <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Navigate to the Validation tab of your agreement.</cmd>
         </step>
         <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Click <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Show More</uicontrol> besides the error description.</cmd>
         </step>
      </steps>
      <postreq class="- topic/section task/postreq ">
         <p class="- topic/p ">Validation Error popup appears with a detailed description of each failed program. You can view the Section Id and Account Name in the error message to identify Participants and Agreement Account.</p>
         <p class="- topic/p ">To download the validation error log file, click the paper clip icon (<image height="23"
                   placement="inline"
                   width="24"
                   href="../attachments/102432724/102432753.png"
                   class="- topic/image "/>) besides the error description.</p>
         <p class="- topic/p ">
            <fig class="- topic/fig ">
               <image height="250"
                      placement="break"
                      width="614"
                      href="../attachments/102432724/102432752.png"
                      class="- topic/image "/>
            </fig>
         </p>
         <note type="note" class="- topic/note ">You need to manually rectify the reason behind the failed validations to activate your agreement. </note>
